Givens:

$\vec{a}=4 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}$

$\vec{v}_i=0 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}\space$ (hare is initially at rest)

$\vec{v}_f=20 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}$

Plug in and solve for $\Delta t$:

$\begin{align} \vec{a} &= \frac{\Delta\vec{v}}{\Delta t}
\\\\
4 \small{\frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}} &= \frac{\vec{v}_f-\vec{v}_i}{\Delta t}
\\\\
4 \small{\frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}} &= \frac{20 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}-0 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}}{\Delta t}
\\\\
4 \small{\frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}} &= \dfrac{20 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}}{\Delta t}
\\\\
\Delta t\times4 \small{\frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}} &= \dfrac{20 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}}{\cancel{\Delta t}} \times\cancel{\Delta t} 
\\\\
\dfrac{\Delta t\times\cancel{4 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}}}{\cancel{4 \frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}}} &= \dfrac{20 \frac{\cancel{\text{m}}}{\cancel{\text{s}}}}{4 \frac{\cancel{\text{m}}}{\text{s}^{\cancel{2}}}}
\\\\
\Delta t &= 5\space\text{s}
\end{align}$
